Barring any last-minute change, the presidential flag bearer of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu will on Wednesday present his running mate, Senator Kashim Shetimma to the National Working Committee (NWC) of the party. Tinubu announced Shettima as his running mate on Sunday, July 4 in Daura, Kastina State after presenting him to President Muhammadu Buhari.   Sam Larry disowns Portable over one million boys…     Akintoye dissolves Ilana Omo Oodua executive council     Caging Kuje escapees   APC National Chairman, Senator Abdullahi Adamu with all NWC members are expected to receive the party’s standard flag bearer and his running mate. The unveiling of Shettima was earlier fixed for last week but postponed without any reason cited. But a source within the party said the ongoing renovation at the National Secretariat may have informed the last-minute postponement.